nib.text:
Seven people were injured during an exchange of gunfire in Lyn-Lake early Thursday morning, police said.

At 12:30 a.m., two people exchanged gunfire outside of a business on the 3000 block of South Lyndale Avenue, according to a report from [WCCO](https://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2021/08/26/shooting-outside-south-minneapolis-business-leaves-7-injured/). 

Police responded to the scene, where they located three people with gunshot wounds. 

Officers later located four people at area hospitals who were also shot at the scene. 

WCCO reported that one of the victims was listed in critical condition and five victims were listed in serious condition. All seven victims are expected to survive their injuries. 

Radio transmissions from the scene indicated a suspect may have fled the scene in a a 2000 GMC Yukon, but no suspect information has been confirmed by Minneapolis Police officials.

No arrests have been made and an investigation is ongoing. 

The investigation will determine if the victims were intended targets, bystanders, or suspects. 

Anyone with information is asked to call CrimeStoppers at 1-800-222-8477.
